kernel_variant.question:
Let $n\ge 2$ be an \emph{even} integer and let $p$ be a prime number.  Denote  
\[
G_{n,p}\;:=\;\bigl\{A\in SL_{n}(\mathbb{F}_{p})\ \bigm|\ \operatorname{tr}A=0\bigr\}.
\tag{$\dagger$}
\]
Two players, \textbf{Alice} and \textbf{Bob}, alternately pick matrices subject to  
\begin{enumerate}
\item the chosen matrix lies in $G_{n,p}$;
\item the same matrix may not be chosen twice;
\item each new matrix must commute with every matrix selected earlier.
\end{enumerate}
A player who has no legal move on her/his turn loses.

For every pair $(n,p)$ with $n$ even, determine which player possesses a winning strategy.

